        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/u/a3d4f5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-06T04:15:33.382Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Ahhh, okay. THANK YOU! <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/megan\">@Megan</a></p>\n<p>I tried this, and it only works on when I swipe up and hit the “Lock” button. If I press and hold  the “Record” button, when I let go, it sends right away.</p>\n<p>This isn’t very intuitive.</p>\n<p>There should be some sort of clear way for us to know how to pause the recording. WhatsApp, for example, when you “Lock” the recording button so you don’t have to keep holding it, it has a clear “Pause” button that you can press. Tapping the screen seems kind of random to me. It’s not a very clean way of pausing the recording so we can preview it.</p>",
