        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/4491bb/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-06T06:11:28.107Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I agree that there should be a way to pause a voice recording and then later be able to pick it up again.</p>\n<p>I suggest giving this topic a like to boost this feature request:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"3357\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/z/50afbb/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/pause-while-recording-voice-message/3357\">Pause while recording voice message</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    When using voice messages to communicate, the speaker may often have to think for a few seconds, thus creating silence. But this silence has no use for the listener. \nIt would be useful if Signal offered a way to pause the recording and then continue it. For example, while holding down the mic button, swipe it up to pause, then swipe it back down to continue (similar to swiping it left to cancel).\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
        "post_number": 4,
